## Actions

### List videos in a channel
```sql
SELECT v.position, v.youtube_id, v.title, v.duration_seconds
FROM videos v
JOIN channels c ON c.id = v.channel_id
WHERE c.slug = '<channel-slug>'
ORDER BY v.position;
```

### Remove a video (by title search or youtube_id)
1. Find the video:
```sql
SELECT v.id, v.title, v.youtube_id, v.position FROM videos v
JOIN channels c ON c.id = v.channel_id
WHERE c.slug = '<channel-slug>' AND (v.title ILIKE '%<search>%' OR v.youtube_id = '<id>');
```
2. Delete it:
```sql
DELETE FROM videos WHERE id = '<video-uuid>';
```
3. Reorder remaining videos to close the gap:
```sql
WITH ranked AS (
  SELECT id, ROW_NUMBER() OVER (ORDER BY position) as new_pos
  FROM videos WHERE channel_id = (SELECT id FROM channels WHERE slug = '<channel-slug>')
)
UPDATE videos SET position = ranked.new_pos FROM ranked WHERE videos.id = ranked.id;
```

### Add a video
1. Get video info from YouTube oEmbed or the user's input
2. Insert:
```sql
INSERT INTO videos (channel_id, youtube_id, title, description, thumbnail_url, duration_seconds, position)
VALUES (
  (SELECT id FROM channels WHERE slug = '<channel-slug>'),
  '<youtube_id>',
  '<title>',
  '<description>',
  'https://img.youtube.com/vi/<youtube_id>/maxresdefault.jpg',
  <duration>,
  <position>
);
```
3. If inserting in the middle, shift positions first:
```sql
UPDATE videos SET position = position + 1
WHERE channel_id = (SELECT id FROM channels WHERE slug = '<channel-slug>')
AND position >= <target_position>;
```

### Reorder a video
```sql
-- Remove from old position, insert at new
-- Step 1: Set target video position to -1 (temp)
UPDATE videos SET position = -1 WHERE id = '<video-uuid>';
-- Step 2: Shift others
UPDATE videos SET position = position - 1
WHERE channel_id = '<channel-id>' AND position > <old_position>;
UPDATE videos SET position = position + 1
WHERE channel_id = '<channel-id>' AND position >= <new_position>;
-- Step 3: Set final position
UPDATE videos SET position = <new_position> WHERE id = '<video-uuid>';
```

### What's on now
Use the schedule logic: playlist loops from half-hour marks. Calculate:
- seconds since last half-hour = (minutes % 30) * 60 + seconds
- walk through video durations to find current video + offset

